headline: US STOCKS-S&P, Dow end slightly up, extend closing streaks despite Disney drag
summary: The S&P 500 and Dow Jones Industrial Average both clung onto gains to ended slightly higher on Tuesday, extending recent winning streaks fueled by renewed expectations that the Federal Reserve will cut interest rates this year.  The advances pushed the S&P 500 to a fourth straight higher close, and its best winning run since March.
